<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-9585] Make &quot;truncate table X&quot; an alias for &quot;truncate X&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9585</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;CQL syntax is inconsistent: it&apos;s &quot;drop table X&quot; but &quot;truncate X&quot;. It used to trip me up all the time until I wrapped my brain around this inconsistency and it still triggers a tiny bout of OCD every time I type it.  I realize it&apos;s too late to change it,  but why not have both? &quot;truncate table X&quot; is also consistent with the syntax in SQL.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12837225">CASSANDRA-9585</key>
            <summary>Make &quot;truncate table X&quot; an alias for &quot;truncate X&quot;</summary>
