                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14736506" author="blerer" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2015 09:06:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch adds: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;an optional &lt;tt&gt;TABLE&lt;/tt&gt; element to the &lt;tt&gt;TRUNCATE&lt;/tt&gt; syntax.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a unit test to verify the behavior&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;updates the CQL documentation and the NEWS.txt&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The unit test results are &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/blerer/job/blerer-9585-2.1-testall/3/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The dtest results are &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/blerer/job/blerer-9585-2.1-dtest/1/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14736507" author="blerer" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2015 09:07:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=snazy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;snazy&quot;&gt;snazy&lt;/a&gt; could you review?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14736536" author="snazy" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2015 09:27:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Two things:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;can you add a test for &lt;tt&gt;TRUNCATE TABLE&lt;/tt&gt; syntax in the unit test?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;please add completion option/syntax enhancement to cqlsh&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure whether we should change CQL syntax in 2.1 - although the change itself is trivial.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14736563" author="blerer" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2015 09:49:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The unit test was already testing both the &lt;tt&gt;TRUNCATE&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;TRUNCATE TABLE&lt;/tt&gt; syntax.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch fix the cqlsh and the documentation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this case, I think that it is ok to change the syntax as it is fully backward compatible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14736575" author="snazy" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2015 09:56:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah - missed the loop over the string array in the unit test. Sorry - you&apos;re right.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Just one nit: in NEWS.txt it should read &quot;TRUNCATE&quot; not &quot;TRUNCAT&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Feel free to fix that on commit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1 on the patch (if cassci is fine)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14736591" author="slebresne" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2015 10:03:40 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I think that it is ok to change the syntax as it is fully backward compatible.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is, adding new syntax is acceptable in a minor release. That said, this should ideally imply a minor bump of the CQL version number, in both &lt;tt&gt;QueryProcessor&lt;/tt&gt; and in the doc (with ideally an entry in the changelog at the end of the doc).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You also have a typo in the &lt;tt&gt;NEWS&lt;/tt&gt; file, and something like &quot;The syntax TRUNCATE TABLE X is now accepted as an alias for TRUNCATE X&quot; would be a tad more informative. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14737060" author="thobbs" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2015 15:44:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;DEFAULT_CQLVER&lt;/tt&gt; in cqlsh also needs to be updated if you bump the version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14737399" author="blerer" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2015 18:53:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
I remembered that one ... when I had 60+ dtests failing on CI &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14738501" author="snazy" created="Thu, 10 Sep 2015 09:39:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, then you should also update CQL version 3.3.0 to 3.3.1 for 2.2 branch as well. Should this version bump noted in &lt;tt&gt;NEWS.txt&lt;/tt&gt;?&lt;br/&gt;
Pushing branches for 2.2, 3.0 and trunk would be great then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14740345" author="blerer" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2015 07:34:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patches bump the CQL version to 3.3.1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the unit test results for 2.1 are &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/blerer/job/blerer-9585-2.1-testall/6/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the dtest results for 2.1 are &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/blerer/job/blerer-9585-2.1-dtest/4/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the unit test results for 2.2 are &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/blerer/job/blerer-9585-2.2-testall/1/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the dtest results for 2.2 are &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/blerer/job/blerer-9585-2.2-dtest/1/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the unit test results for 3.0 are &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/blerer/job/blerer-9585-3.0-testall/1/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the dtest results for 3.0 are &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/blerer/job/blerer-9585-3.0-dtest/1/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14740349" author="blerer" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2015 07:36:30 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt; Should this version bump noted in NEWS.txt?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I checked the &lt;tt&gt;NEWS.txt&lt;/tt&gt; and it does not seems that we have done that in the past.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14790995" author="snazy" created="Wed, 16 Sep 2015 19:27:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry for being late with my answer.&lt;br/&gt;
+1 on it then&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
